1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:28,450
♪Like a flock of birds
pressing ever forward♪

2
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:33,350
♪Stranded on an island
shrouded in heavy mist♪

3
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:38,410
♪We may seem small
beneath the vast world♪

4
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:43,680
♪But not once have we felt despair♪

5
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,770
♪We've crossed waves
a thousand layers deep♪

6
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,530
♪Stepped on reefs hidden in the dark♪

7
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:54,730
♪Facing sharper winds head-on♪

8
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:57,660
♪Our wounds now stitched
into battle robes♪

9
00:00:57,660 --> 00:01:00,370
♪The long night
is branded by starlight♪

10
00:01:00,370 --> 00:01:05,440
♪We embrace this deep blue together♪

11
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:10,620
♪At the edge of the vast unknown,
I remain unchanged♪

12
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:16,540
♪Holding fast with lonely courage,
roaring without fear♪

13
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:21,850
♪Determined to be
both my friend and my rival♪

14
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:27,030
♪No one dares to blindly
urge me to turn back♪

15
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:32,090
♪I choose what I believe is worth it♪

16
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:38,340
=Rose and Gun=

17
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 31=

18
00:01:55,570 --> 00:01:58,440
(Next time you pass by,
I might already be gone.)

19
00:01:59,226 --> 00:02:01,950
(But my country will still stand tall
like the Five Great Mountains.)

20
00:02:02,210 --> 00:02:05,210
(The rivers will still keep
rushing toward the east.)

21
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,570
(The will of the people
will always move forward.)

22
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:11,093
(Wenzhou Anti-Smuggling Bureau Letter)
(Just like the rising sun.)

23
00:02:11,410 --> 00:02:12,570
(Just like you.)

24
00:02:13,650 --> 00:02:16,640
♪The sound of the ocean breeze♪

25
00:02:17,490 --> 00:02:20,550
♪Feels like a letter back from you♪

26
00:02:21,490 --> 00:02:26,500
♪The distance between us slowly fades♪

27
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:33,940
(IOU)

28
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:41,390
♪Please don't ask how much I miss you♪

29
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:43,600
Mom, what did Dad write?

30
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:51,220
♪Goodbye... Goodbye...♪

31
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:54,900
(Next time you pass by,
I might already be gone.)

32
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:59,140
(Wu Tongshu)

33
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,920
(My dear wife and son,)

34
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:04,160
(the sea is how I'm watching over you.)

35
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:07,982
(The sea is how I'm holding you close.)

36
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:12,520
♪When I stride alone in the world♪

37
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:18,580
(Wenzhou Anti-Smuggling Bureau Letter)

38
00:03:18,580 --> 00:03:20,740
♪Why must we part ways?♪

39
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:46,570
I'm home.

40
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:38,990
Captain Wu.

41
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:43,890
I'm tired.

42
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:08,250
Auntie, when did you get to Wenzhou?

43
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:10,030
I just got here a few days ago.

44
00:05:10,290 --> 00:05:11,870
I heard Wu Si was coming back,

45
00:05:11,870 --> 00:05:13,260
so I took some time off

46
00:05:13,260 --> 00:05:14,240
and came right over.

47
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,750
Where are you staying?

48
00:05:16,848 --> 00:05:19,060
If you don't mind,
you're welcome to stay at our place.

49
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:20,300
Thanks, but no need.

50
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:22,300
I won't be here long anyway.

51
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:24,540
I've already settled in at a hotel.

52
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,848
Don't worry about me.

53
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:29,370
So,

54
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:31,700
you've seen Wu Si?

55
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,180
Yes, I have.

56
00:05:35,380 --> 00:05:37,260
I was right there the day

57
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:38,700
you two were on the phone.

58
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,420
Tang Xin, can I ask you something?

59
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:44,740
What exactly

60
00:05:45,180 --> 00:05:47,060
happened between you two?

61
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:55,740
Auntie, actually,

62
00:05:56,740 --> 00:05:58,260
before Wu Si left,

63
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:59,620
he proposed to me.

64
00:06:01,180 --> 00:06:02,180
At the time,

65
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:04,260
I wanted to wait
until he got back safely

66
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,500
before I said yes.

67
00:06:07,260 --> 00:06:08,500
But I didn't expect

68
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,620
things would be so different

69
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:12,300
after he came back.

70
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:14,620
The proposal doesn't count anymore.

71
00:06:14,620 --> 00:06:16,060
He keeps avoiding me.

72
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:17,730
I honestly don't know why.

73
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:21,060
Tang Xin.

74
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:23,580
Wu Si's father

75
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:26,060
died when Wu Si was still very young.

76
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,620
Wu Si told me about him once.

77
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:32,740
His dad used to be in the Navy.

78
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:35,380
Then, he switched careers
and became a police officer.

79
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:38,860
He specialized in cracking down
on maritime smuggling.

80
00:06:39,060 --> 00:06:40,420
Because of work,

81
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:42,560
he went undercover
under a false name for ten months.

82
00:06:42,626 --> 00:06:44,940
I waited all that time for him
to come back

83
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:46,860
so we could be a family again

84
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:49,060
and finally live a normal life.

85
00:06:50,380 --> 00:06:51,860
But then one day...

86
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:55,700
Hello?

87
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:57,180
Hello? Son?

88
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,140
Dad!

89
00:06:58,140 --> 00:07:00,140
Mom, come quick! It's Dad!

90
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:01,700
I'm coming!

91
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:04,060
Dad, when are you coming home?

92
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:05,820
Do you want a game console or something?

93
00:07:05,820 --> 00:07:07,620
No, I don't want a game console.

94
00:07:07,620 --> 00:07:09,500
I just want Dad to come home.

95
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:12,420
Dad, when are you coming back?

96
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:13,740
Here, let me talk.

97
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:17,060
Hello?

98
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:18,820
Tongshu?

99
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:21,380
I got the day off today.

100
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:23,850
Which store were you thinking of?

101
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:25,260
I'll take our son.

102
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:29,020
I compared prices
at a bunch of places last time.

103
00:07:29,820 --> 00:07:33,180
That shop near Liubu was selling it
for 273 yuan.

104
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:36,260
The one in Luzhuang was 238 yuan.

105
00:07:36,860 --> 00:07:38,020
None of them would bargain.

106
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,500
Even after talking it over,

107
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,820
they only knocked off five yuan.

108
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:41,820
(Hospital memo)

109
00:07:41,820 --> 00:07:44,860
You have to buy the battery-powered
game card separately.

110
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:47,260
And if you end up with a fake one,

111
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:48,982
the battery drains super fast.

112
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:52,380
You'll need a new battery
every seventeen or eighteen hours.

113
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:56,420
There are so many types

114
00:07:56,860 --> 00:07:58,260
of game consoles now.

115
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:00,820
Which one are you looking for?

116
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:04,380
That photo Liu
gave me has its picture.

117
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:07,060
There are tons of stores.
It's hard to find.

118
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:09,500
I even started off
walking the wrong way.

119
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:11,180
You should ask someone.

120
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:13,260
Okay.

121
00:08:14,380 --> 00:08:15,500
I got it.

122
00:08:18,260 --> 00:08:19,140
Honey.

123
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:22,620
I had a dream about you and our son.

124
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:25,620
I really wish I could come home.

125
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:29,060
I just want to see you both again.

126
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:33,804
Can you put our son on the phone?

127
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:39,020
Sure.

128
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,380
Hey, sweetheart.

129
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:45,340
The sun is shining so brightly today.

130
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:48,140
I'm going to take a little nap.

131
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:50,860
Say goodnight

132
00:08:51,380 --> 00:08:52,650
to Daddy.

133
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:55,380
Goodnight, Dad. Goodnight. Goodnight.

134
00:09:01,660 --> 00:09:02,500
Tongshu...

135
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:05,620
Tongshu!

136
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:12,380
Before he went undercover,

137
00:09:12,380 --> 00:09:15,140
we made a deal
to use "game console" as a code word.

138
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:17,260
If he ever called

139
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:19,620
and said he was buying one for our son,

140
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,100
that would mean his cover was blown.

141
00:09:24,540 --> 00:09:27,340
That was the last call he ever made.

142
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:28,900
He slipped in a message

143
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:31,260
with the coordinates for Liubu Reef
and Luzhuang Reef.

144
00:09:31,271 --> 00:09:32,540
He was off by just a few degrees.

145
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:34,780
The smugglers' boat was
moving at 17 or 18 knots.

146
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:37,500
I told Liu right away that the coast
guard had gone the wrong way.

147
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:39,340
I called the police immediately,

148
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:42,020
but by the time they got there,
it was already too late.

149
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:43,260
Tang Xin...

150
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:46,860
The reason I came to talk to you today

151
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,220
is because of all this.

152
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:52,100
The way Wu Si changed after the drill...

153
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,980
might be connected

154
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:57,140
to everything our family has
gone through over the years.

155
00:09:58,780 --> 00:10:00,340
During this exercise,

156
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:02,500
he probably went through

157
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:06,020
some danger or loss
we'll never know about.

158
00:10:06,660 --> 00:10:08,260
That could be why he changed.

159
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:10,740
I think

160
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:12,780
maybe he's scared.

161
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:15,460
He's afraid that one day,

162
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:18,340
he might not come home,
just like his father.

163
00:10:21,620 --> 00:10:22,740
He's also afraid

164
00:10:23,780 --> 00:10:25,080
that your future

165
00:10:26,140 --> 00:10:27,540
might end up like mine.

166
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:33,100
Brigadier.

167
00:10:33,460 --> 00:10:34,020
It's me.

168
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:35,937
The Armed Police called.

169
00:10:37,780 --> 00:10:38,780
It's about Zong Qing?

170
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:40,260
Put it through now.

171
00:10:40,380 --> 00:10:40,780
Yes, Sir.

172
00:10:44,460 --> 00:10:47,020
The reason I brought all this up today

173
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,340
is just to remind you

174
00:10:49,380 --> 00:10:50,740
that before you decide

175
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:54,260
to marry a soldier,

176
00:10:54,380 --> 00:10:55,740
you really should

177
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,540
think everything through carefully.

178
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:01,260
Auntie,

179
00:11:01,990 --> 00:11:04,780
allow me to ask a serious question.

180
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:09,260
If I want to marry Wu Si,

181
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:11,380
would you approve?

182
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:14,380
As a soldier's wife?

183
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:15,980
No, I wouldn't.

184
00:11:18,380 --> 00:11:20,460
Because if someone objects,

185
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:23,260
it'll push you both
to think it over more seriously.

186
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:31,260
But as Wu Si's mother...

187
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,340
I give you my blessing.

188
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:53,930
Thank you, Auntie.

189
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:00,900
(Brigadier)

190
00:12:04,180 --> 00:12:05,420
(Brigadier)

191
00:12:07,140 --> 00:12:07,860
Brigadier.

192
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:09,780
Return to base.

193
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:11,980
Now?

194
00:12:12,620 --> 00:12:14,260
Cheng Yuan used to lead

195
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:15,620
the sniper training.

196
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:17,380
This year, it's your turn.

197
00:12:17,860 --> 00:12:18,780
But Brigadier,

198
00:12:18,826 --> 00:12:20,960
(Chinese People's Liberation Army)
my test results aren't back yet.

199
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:22,780
No need to wait for them.

200
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:23,780
You're fine.

201
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:24,740
Really?

202
00:12:25,020 --> 00:12:26,020
How can that be?

203
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:28,380
The Armed Police
double-checked everything.

204
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:30,540
That drug dealer wasn't even

205
00:12:30,540 --> 00:12:32,020
HIV positive.

206
00:12:33,660 --> 00:12:35,380
Understood. I'll get ready to head back.

207
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:41,740
That's a relief.

208
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,020
I was terrified.

209
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:46,380
Lan Yangyang,

210
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:49,380
that was not how you sounded.

211
00:12:51,260 --> 00:12:53,740
I really thought
you weren't scared at all.

212
00:12:54,380 --> 00:12:55,780
Of course I was scared.

213
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,660
I just didn't want you
to get more nervous.

214
00:12:58,260 --> 00:12:59,660
You were already so worried.

215
00:12:59,660 --> 00:13:02,260
If I panicked too,
you'd be even worse off.

216
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:07,620
Alright.

217
00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:10,900
That's behind us now.

218
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:12,860
Honey...

219
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,220
I want to have another baby.

220
00:13:19,740 --> 00:13:21,380
I want one too.

221
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:24,500
But...

222
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:27,020
I've given it some serious thought.

223
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:30,500
I want to be better prepared

224
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:31,980
this time.

225
00:13:32,860 --> 00:13:35,620
I don't want to be
all over the place like last time.

226
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,980
I want to grow up first,
and stand on my own two feet.

227
00:13:41,182 --> 00:13:42,740
Let's wait until we're both more ready

228
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:43,740
before we try again.

229
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:58,740
Retirement ceremony, begin.

230
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:02,860
Play and sing the national anthem
of the People's Republic of China.

231
00:14:10,860 --> 00:14:15,020
♪Stand up!
Those who refuse to be slaves♪

232
00:14:15,220 --> 00:14:20,620
♪With our flesh and blood,
let's build our newest Great Wall♪

233
00:14:21,220 --> 00:14:24,500
♪The Chinese Nation♪

234
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:27,100
♪Is at its greatest peril♪

235
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:29,740
♪Each one is forced to let out♪

236
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:31,860
♪One last roar♪

237
00:14:32,340 --> 00:14:36,260
♪Stand up! Stand up! Stand up♪

238
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,860
♪We are billions of one heart♪

239
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:42,740
♪Braving the enemies' fire, march on♪

240
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:45,500
♪Braving the enemies' fire♪

241
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:50,380
♪March on♪

242
00:14:51,740 --> 00:14:53,260
Present the flag.

243
00:14:57,380 --> 00:14:58,620
March in step.

244
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:03,930
Salute.

245
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,140
Salute complete.

246
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:23,940
(List of Retired Soldiers)

247
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:29,780
Order from the Navy Special Operations
Brigade of the PLA Marine Corps.

248
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:32,340
In accordance
with the Military Service Law,

249
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:36,740
and the Regulations on Active Service
for Soldiers of the PLA,

250
00:15:38,140 --> 00:15:42,140
the following personnel are approved
for discharge from active duty.

251
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,220
Staff Sergeant Wang Jun.

252
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:44,900
Yes!

253
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:46,460
Staff Sergeant Li Tianjie.

254
00:15:46,460 --> 00:15:47,493
(Honorably retired)
Yes!

255
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:49,380
Private First Class Wu Ke'er.

256
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:50,140
Yes!

257
00:15:50,460 --> 00:15:51,260
Present the flowers.

258
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:08,020
Alright.

259
00:16:09,380 --> 00:16:10,020
Thank you.

260
00:16:13,380 --> 00:16:15,980
You never forget to say thank you.

261
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:18,020
Once you're back in the army,

262
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:20,260
are you going to give me a salute too?

263
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:23,980
I'm not going back.

264
00:16:29,604 --> 00:16:30,471
Taking off the badge.

265
00:16:58,740 --> 00:17:00,740
Thank you all
for your loyalty and service.

266
00:17:02,226 --> 00:17:03,140
You've done well.

267
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:07,820
I must...

268
00:17:09,982 --> 00:17:11,500
thank you for looking out for me.

269
00:17:14,260 --> 00:17:15,060
Don't mention it.

270
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:20,340
You're not going back to the army.

271
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:22,260
So, what's the plan now?

272
00:17:22,820 --> 00:17:24,260
Taking my girlfriend home.

273
00:17:25,248 --> 00:17:26,540
Spending some time with her.

274
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:28,420
And with my parents too.

275
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:32,260
Make sure to invite us
when you two get married.

