still in the Roman Islands.

471
00:30:19,900 --> 00:30:22,070
Besides the Aston Hotel,
they're mainly active

472
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:23,500
around the Atocha Company.

473
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:26,020
Mr. Lin.

474
00:30:26,020 --> 00:30:28,500
Did you find anything else

475
00:30:28,700 --> 00:30:29,590
that is suspicious?

476
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:32,980
There's a foreigner
who meets him at the hotel a lot.

477
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:34,780
His name is William.

478
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:37,060
I had a friend help me look into him.

479
00:30:37,660 --> 00:30:39,580
Turns out he runs a smuggling ring.

480
00:30:40,020 --> 00:30:41,300
He's on Interpol's wanted list.

481
00:30:48,020 --> 00:30:49,500
Seriously, Zong Qing?

482
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:52,260
This is the dinner
you're treating me to?

483
00:30:56,060 --> 00:30:57,420
Fine, just spill it.

484
00:30:57,426 --> 00:30:58,893
I know you have something to say.

485
00:31:01,020 --> 00:31:02,060
You know me too well.

486
00:31:05,420 --> 00:31:06,540
Captain is not joining

487
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:08,404
this round of training.
He's still recovering.

488
00:31:09,580 --> 00:31:11,500
That's his business.
You don't need to tell me.

489
00:31:13,660 --> 00:31:14,540
Xin...

490
00:31:15,300 --> 00:31:16,540
Just give him one more chance.

491
00:31:16,540 --> 00:31:18,340
It's not that I won't give him a chance.

492
00:31:19,420 --> 00:31:21,020
He is choosing to give up on me.

493
00:31:23,780 --> 00:31:24,780
And here I am,

494
00:31:24,780 --> 00:31:27,300
still daydreaming
about a future with him.

495
00:31:28,100 --> 00:31:30,340
But I was never even part of his plans.

496
00:31:45,540 --> 00:31:46,300
What's this?

497
00:31:53,820 --> 00:31:54,740
He wrote it.

498
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:56,260
For you.

499
00:32:00,340 --> 00:32:03,500
(To Tang Xi.
If you're reading this, I'm with you.)

500
00:32:05,020 --> 00:32:06,580
(If you got this letter,)

501
00:32:07,500 --> 00:32:09,780
(you've probably
also gotten some bad news.)

502
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:14,300
(I'm sorry I left
without saying goodbye.)

503
00:32:16,020 --> 00:32:19,740
(Life wasn't long,
but I gave it my all.)

504
00:32:20,693 --> 00:32:22,260
(I don't regret joining the military.)

505
00:32:23,060 --> 00:32:24,980
(I don't regret meeting you either.)

506
00:32:25,540 --> 00:32:27,220
(I fought the battles I had to.)

507
00:32:27,220 --> 00:32:29,180
(I kept the right values.)

508
00:32:29,660 --> 00:32:31,740
(I've loved with all I had.)

509
00:32:33,540 --> 00:32:35,420
(The ending doesn't really matter.)

510
00:32:35,940 --> 00:32:37,020
(Whenever you miss me,)

511
00:32:37,660 --> 00:32:39,100
(I'll come back to see you.)

512
00:32:40,260 --> 00:32:43,020
(My pure and loyal love for you)

513
00:32:44,020 --> 00:32:46,500
(will never end. Salute.)

514
00:32:48,340 --> 00:32:49,180
What's this?

515
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,300
It's a military tradition.

516
00:32:55,340 --> 00:32:57,100
When we get assigned to

517
00:32:57,580 --> 00:32:59,020
special missions,

518
00:32:59,180 --> 00:33:00,740
we write letters of intent.

519
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:02,780
Then,

520
00:33:04,137 --> 00:33:06,100
they're usually addressed
to immediate family.

521
00:33:06,780 --> 00:33:08,500
If we make it back,

522
00:33:09,340 --> 00:33:11,180
the letter just gets returned to us.

523
00:33:11,500 --> 00:33:12,740
But if we don't...

524
00:33:14,820 --> 00:33:16,300
It gets delivered

525
00:33:16,580 --> 00:33:17,740
with the notice of death.

526
00:33:19,420 --> 00:33:20,060
Xin.

527
00:33:20,500 --> 00:33:23,060
The letters Captain wrote
to his mom...

528
00:33:23,060 --> 00:33:24,260
barely changed over the years.

529
00:33:24,780 --> 00:33:26,740
But ever since you two got together,

530
00:33:28,740 --> 00:33:30,700
he's wanted to add you to the letter.

531
00:33:32,500 --> 00:33:33,740
Honestly,

532
00:33:35,060 --> 00:33:35,780
he was ready

533
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:37,540
to say goodbye to you the hard way.

534
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:39,740
He told us

535
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:42,820
that if anything ever happened to him,

536
00:33:43,180 --> 00:33:45,020
we should give you
the most recent letter.

537
00:33:46,780 --> 00:33:48,780
(Wu Si)

538
00:33:50,540 --> 00:33:51,780
How many letters has he written?

539
00:33:53,060 --> 00:33:54,340
Scroll through and see.

540
00:33:59,260 --> 00:34:01,860
(To Tang Xi.
If you're reading this, I'm with you.)

541
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:03,100
Xin.

542
00:34:03,460 --> 00:34:04,580
To be honest, every time

543
00:34:04,740 --> 00:34:05,900
he had to leave you,

544
00:34:05,900 --> 00:34:08,060
he acted like it was the last goodbye.

545
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:09,540
Like he still had more to say.

546
00:34:09,540 --> 00:34:11,340
That is why the letters

547
00:34:11,340 --> 00:34:12,540
just kept getting longer,

548
00:34:12,620 --> 00:34:14,060
like each one was the last one

549
00:34:14,060 --> 00:34:15,820
he'd ever write.

550
00:34:18,140 --> 00:34:20,060
We used to tease him all the time.

551
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:22,140
"Captain, it's not the end of the world.

552
00:34:22,140 --> 00:34:23,820
What's with all the dramatic letters?"

553
00:34:24,420 --> 00:34:25,020
But you know...

554
00:34:27,782 --> 00:34:29,448
You'll get it once you read it.

555
00:34:30,380 --> 00:34:32,259
(If my sacrifice
can buy you peace, it's worth it.)

556
00:34:32,259 --> 00:34:33,860
(To Tang Xin.
This letter isn't a goodbye.)

557
00:34:36,300 --> 00:34:37,300
Go ahead and read it.

558
00:34:39,060 --> 00:34:40,380
All of these

559
00:34:41,140 --> 00:34:43,340
are the future he didn't get to live.

560
00:34:45,226 --> 00:34:46,700
The ones he imagined with you.

561
00:34:51,500 --> 00:34:52,140
Xin.

562
00:34:52,140 --> 00:34:54,020
There's one thing
I should correct you on.

563
00:34:55,540 --> 00:34:57,220
To Captain,

564
00:34:58,780 --> 00:35:00,540
you've already been part of his future.

565
00:35:03,493 --> 00:35:05,020
It's not that he didn't trust you.

566
00:35:05,500 --> 00:35:06,780
He just didn't trust himself.

567
00:35:12,820 --> 00:35:14,340
This might sound kind of dramatic,

568
00:35:14,500 --> 00:35:16,380
but for people in our line of work...

569
00:35:20,780 --> 00:35:22,820
Finding a sense of safety
in the person you love

570
00:35:24,500 --> 00:35:25,540
means everything.

571
00:35:37,580 --> 00:35:38,980
Dating someone like you guys

572
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:40,340
doesn't even feel like dating.

573
00:35:42,060 --> 00:35:43,780
It's like being tested to the core.

574
00:35:44,820 --> 00:35:47,100
And marrying someone like you guys

575
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:49,300
is basically a survival challenge.

576
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:53,620
If it's a challenge,

577
00:35:53,620 --> 00:35:54,937
then why not go all in, right?

578
00:35:55,540 --> 00:35:57,020
Your relationship with Captain

579
00:35:59,980 --> 00:36:01,140
is not too late to be fixed.

580
00:36:13,060 --> 00:36:13,780
Honey.

581
00:36:13,980 --> 00:36:15,620
Make sure you eat well while I'm gone.

582
00:36:15,715 --> 00:36:17,060
I made your favorite dumplings.

583
00:36:17,060 --> 00:36:18,060
They're in the freezer.

584
00:36:18,060 --> 00:36:19,271
Boil them when you're hungry.

585
00:36:19,293 --> 00:36:20,020
Honey.

586
00:36:21,060 --> 00:36:22,580
When you get back this time,

587
00:36:24,300 --> 00:36:25,580
let's move somewhere new.

588
00:36:26,620 --> 00:36:28,220
I don't want to stay here anymore.

589
00:36:28,980 --> 00:36:29,820
Why?

590
00:36:33,540 --> 00:36:35,500
Didn't you decorate this place yourself?

591
00:36:35,580 --> 00:36:36,820
Why don't you want to stay?

592
00:36:37,220 --> 00:36:39,420
This place is full of
memories of us being apart.

593
00:36:41,540 --> 00:36:43,060
We barely

594
00:36:43,300 --> 00:36:45,100
had any time together here.

595
00:36:46,500 --> 00:36:48,340
You were always leaving
or reporting back in.

596
00:36:48,860 --> 00:36:51,020
At first, I was the one
always home alone.

597
00:36:52,340 --> 00:36:54,060
Now I'm working,

598
00:36:54,540 --> 00:36:56,020
and you're the one here by yourself.

599
00:36:59,340 --> 00:37:00,820
I don't like it here anymore.

600
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:03,620
Honey.

601
00:37:04,580 --> 00:37:06,060
Don't get stuck on the sad stuff.

602
00:37:06,100 --> 00:37:08,060
Think about all the good times we had.

603
00:37:08,060 --> 00:37:08,780
Right?

604
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:09,820
You remember?

605
00:37:10,220 --> 00:37:11,500
We played games together,

606
00:37:11,604 --> 00:37:12,500
cooked meals together,

607
00:37:12,820 --> 00:37:14,780
and you even blew up the pot once!

608
00:37:15,100 --> 00:37:16,540
We cuddled up to sleep.

609
00:37:16,604 --> 00:37:17,620
Those were good times.

610
00:37:17,780 --> 00:37:19,540
But you're leaving again.

611
00:37:20,300 --> 00:37:22,220
I don't want to be here alone.

612
00:37:22,340 --> 00:37:23,420
This place just feels empty.

613
00:37:25,900 --> 00:37:27,620
If that's how you feel,

614
00:37:27,671 --> 00:37:29,500
you could stay
with Mom and Dad for a while.

615
00:37:29,540 --> 00:37:31,700
I promise I'll be back real soon.

616
00:37:32,020 --> 00:37:32,700
Once I'm back,

617
00:37:32,700 --> 00:37:34,340
we can move wherever you want.

618
00:37:34,340 --> 00:37:36,060
I'll help you set the place up, okay?

619
00:37:57,420 --> 00:37:58,100
Stay safe.

620
00:37:58,380 --> 00:37:59,100
Got it.

621
00:37:59,540 --> 00:38:01,020
I've taken the members away,

622
00:38:01,060 --> 00:38:02,315
so think about your future.

623
00:38:03,660 --> 00:38:04,660
What future?

624
00:38:05,540 --> 00:38:06,820
Don't play dumb with me.

625
00:38:06,820 --> 00:38:08,020
Yangyang told me everything.

626
00:38:08,020 --> 00:38:09,700
We're all waiting for you to marry Xin.

627
00:38:09,780 --> 00:38:10,715
You'd better step up.

628
00:38:11,780 --> 00:38:12,620
Get lost.

629
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:14,020
I'm off.

630
00:38:17,060 --> 00:38:17,900
All missions

631
00:38:17,900 --> 00:38:20,004
must be carried out
with safety as the top priority.

632
00:38:20,026 --> 00:38:20,780
Got that?

633
00:38:21,220 --> 00:38:21,820
Yes.

634
00:38:21,982 --> 00:38:23,300
You don't have to see me off.

635
00:38:25,340 --> 00:38:27,620
Go for it. I believe in you.

636
00:38:30,540 --> 00:38:31,300
Hurry up.

637
00:38:34,900 --> 00:38:35,900
I'll keep this for him.

638
00:38:36,004 --> 00:38:37,980
If you train hard,
you'll earn your snacks.

639
00:38:38,220 --> 00:38:38,900
Yes!

640
00:38:42,100 --> 00:38:43,300
(Tang Xin: Didn't you want to break up?)

641
00:38:43,300 --> 00:38:44,980
(Let's meet and talk it through.
Then I'll agree.)

642
00:38:44,982 --> 00:38:45,671
Get on the truck.

643
00:38:46,700 --> 00:38:47,980
I'm off then, Captain Chen.

644
00:38:48,420 --> 00:38:48,900
Bye.

645
00:38:48,900 --> 00:38:49,500
Go on.

646
00:39:07,500 --> 00:39:08,180
Ke'er.

647
00:39:10,020 --> 00:39:11,340
Cheng Yuan, you're here.

648
00:39:12,340 --> 00:39:13,540
Why'd you ask me to meet here?

649
00:39:14,020 --> 00:39:14,860
Where is this anyway?

650
00:39:15,020 --> 00:39:16,020
It's a park.

651
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:18,220
You finally caught a break from work,

652
00:39:18,220 --> 00:39:19,340
and I've been discharged too.

653
00:39:19,620 --> 00:39:22,100
We finally have time together at last.

654
00:39:22,620 --> 00:39:24,580
Yeah, that doesn't happen often.

655
00:39:25,900 --> 00:39:27,380
So where do you want to go today?

656
00:39:27,660 --> 00:39:28,460
I'll go with you.

657
00:39:29,500 --> 00:39:32,620
I've served in this city for two years.

658
00:39:33,540 --> 00:39:36,220
You could say I know it well,

659
00:39:36,220 --> 00:39:38,780
but it still feels unfamiliar somehow.

660
00:39:38,980 --> 00:39:40,900
We've never had time

661
00:39:41,020 --> 00:39:42,980
to just walk around
and explore together.

662
00:39:43,660 --> 00:39:45,020
Before I leave,

663
00:39:45,460 --> 00:39:48,180
I want us to say goodbye
to Wenzhou together.

664
00:39:48,540 --> 00:39:49,580
And how do we do that?

665
00:40:06,340 --> 00:40:08,700
Excuse me, Sir. Are you Mr. Wu Si?

666
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:10,980
Yes, I am.

667
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:45,690
♪The vast sky and sea,
this deep blue expanse♪

668
00:40:46,810 --> 00:40:49,690
♪So deep, so boundless♪

669
00:40:50,380 --> 00:40:52,300
♪Just like your arms♪

670
00:40:52,380 --> 00:40:53,340
Does it look good?

671
00:40:55,500 --> 00:40:56,220
Yeah, it does.

672
00:40:58,420 --> 00:40:59,980
Is there anything you want to tell me?

673
00:41:00,980 --> 00:41:02,890
♪Even the long, long road♪

674
00:41:04,820 --> 00:41:06,220
I missed you a lot.

675
00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:10,860
I missed you every single day.

676
00:41:11,580 --> 00:41:13,260
Then, why would you break up with me?

677
00:41:13,260 --> 00:41:16,050
♪You speak of dreams
with such calm simplicity♪

678
00:41:16,540 --> 00:41:17,660
Just because we broke up,

679
00:41:19,020 --> 00:41:20,340
doesn't mean I can't miss you.

680
00:41:23,710 --> 00:41:25,800
♪I truly understand♪

681
00:41:27,940 --> 00:41:29,540
You kept avoiding me.

682
00:41:31,100 --> 00:41:32,060
Happy now?

683
00:41:36,020 --> 00:41:37,240
You gave me the cold shoulder.

684
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:40,260
♪Using up all my fortune♪♪

685
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:41,060
Feeling satisfied?

686
00:41:41,060 --> 00:41:44,160
♪Just to trade a lifetime with you♪

687
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:47,360
♪Thank you for awakening♪

688
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:51,590
♪The courage once hidden in my fear♪

689
00:41:51,590 --> 00:41:54,650
♪Turning every chance into certainty♪

690
00:41:55,130 --> 00:41:58,630
♪Turning every tie into companionship♪

691
00:41:58,830 --> 00:42:03,730
♪Blooming into brilliance
for all the years to come♪

692
00:42:03,730 --> 00:42:07,640
♪No one can tear us apart♪

693
00:42:07,910 --> 00:42:11,250
♪Each time my palm feels warm again♪

694
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:16,860
♪The memories return,
and I'm no longer alone♪

695
00:42:17,750 --> 00:42:21,810
♪No matter how far
across time and space♪

696
00:42:22,050 --> 00:42:25,340
♪My longing reaches you in silence♪

697
00:42:25,590 --> 00:42:30,130
♪No need to call out loudly♪

698
00:42:30,130 --> 00:42:32,690
♪Using up all my fortune♪

699
00:42:33,940 --> 00:42:35,380
I read that letters you wrote.

700
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:38,880
♪Thank you for awakening♪

701
00:42:38,900 --> 00:42:40,560
I read them
like they were love letters.

702
00:42:40,582 --> 00:42:44,400
♪The courage once hidden in my fear♪

703
00:42:44,448 --> 00:42:45,750
Don't write stuff like that again.

704
00:42:47,950 --> 00:42:49,930
♪Turning every tie into companionship♪

705
00:42:50,060 --> 00:42:51,860
If you have something to say,

706
00:42:53,540 --> 00:42:55,460
write me a real love letter next time.

707
00:42:58,220 --> 00:43:00,930
♪No matter how much it takes♪

708
00:43:00,930 --> 00:43:05,150
♪To bring this drifting heart to shore♪

709
00:43:05,320 --> 00:43:09,360
♪Thank you for standing behind me♪

710
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:12,740
♪Lighting up the darkness and despair♪

711
00:43:13,893 --> 00:43:15,300
Do I look like I gained weight?

712
00:43:17,940 --> 00:43:18,660
You didn't.

713
00:43:20,380 --> 00:43:25,020
I'm starving.
I haven't eaten meat in days.

714
00:43:26,220 --> 00:43:29,300
I just wanted to look nice
in this wedding dress

715
00:43:29,300 --> 00:43:31,900
so we could take our wedding photos.

716
00:43:49,660 --> 00:43:51,300
You promised me before you left.

717
00:43:53,860 --> 00:43:55,060
Now that you're back...

718
00:43:58,420 --> 00:44:00,100
Can you keep that promise?

719
00:44:37,341 --> 00:44:40,821
♪The vast sky and sea,
this deep blue expanse♪

720
00:44:41,511 --> 00:44:44,781
♪So deep, so boundless♪

721
00:44:45,121 --> 00:44:48,291
♪Just like your arms♪

722
00:44:48,781 --> 00:44:51,901
♪Shielding me from the dark clouds♪

723
00:44:52,191 --> 00:44:55,831
♪Always bearing it all in silence♪

724
00:44:55,831 --> 00:45:02,251
♪Even the long, long road gives me peace
when you're there♪

725
